The paper deals with information measures and their relationship with algorithmic complexity, which are topics that are commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses probability distributions and their computability, which are relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper touches on the convergence of entropy measures, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
